The paper deals with computational complexity in the context of auction theory and mechanism design, which are central topics in game theory and algorithmic game theory. The paper's focus on revenue optimization and pricing strategies suggests that it is likely to be classified under cs.GT (Game Theory) or cs.EC (Economics and Computation). The paper also involves the analysis of distributions and the computation of optimal solutions, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's use of reductions from the SQRT-SUM problem suggests that it could also be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
